SCHIZO THRED I remember @GRITCULT postin about how a kung-fu master never teaches his best student all moves/tricks, and always leaves one secret - for the case in which the student decides to kill him. Someone noted that this meant that one kung-fu move is lost every generation

-selves are useful, but combined with other moves lead to failure - This would create a system a bit similar to inhibitory enzymes in biology / biochemistry - very curious. The ultimate way would be two masters to combine their students and teach students random mix of 2 arts...

I have been theoretizing how this can be potentially solved - one way is to fragment the knowledge and teach different students different parts of the whole - but this still leaves open the possibility of the students "unionizing" and defragmenting the knowledge - so doesnt work!
I think this also starts to resemble genetics a lot with time, very curious topic to think about, even though I did not explain properly. End of thred
